PRIVACY NOTICE
Effective: September 27, 2021
Last Updated: March 8, 2023
Casio Computer Co., Ltd., a Japanese company whose registered office is at 6-2, Hon-machi 1-chome, Shibuya-ku, Tokyo 151-8543, Japan ("
Casio
", "
we
", "
us
",
"our
") takes the protection of your personal data extremely seriously. This Privacy Notice ("
Privacy Notice
") describes how Casio processes and protects your personal data that are any information relating to an identifiable natural person ("
Personal Data
") collected and processed when using our app, CASIO WATCHES ("
App
"). This Privacy Notice also explains your rights to your Personal Data and how you can reach us to get answers to questions you may have about our privacy practices.
This Privacy Notice exclusively applies to the processing of your Personal Data when using our App. This Privacy Notice does not apply to the processing of your Personal Data when creating and using CASIO ID (“CASIO ID”), the user account that allows you to centrally store and manage master data and functions as your access key across various offerings, solely and/or other apps we provide. Such processing is governed by other privacy policies, so when using CASIO ID with this App,
the privacy notice for CASIO ID
applies to you additionally.
Please read the following carefully to understand how we will process your Personal Data provided via your use of the App.
1. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about or in connection with this Privacy Notice (including any request to access, review, obtain a copy of, update, or delete your Personal Data or cease further collection, processing or use thereof, withdraw your consent hereby) or would like to complain about our handling of your Personal Data or exercise any of your rights under the applicable laws regard to the processing of your Personal Data (see paragraph 14 below), please contact us and/or our data protection officer ("
DPO
") by using the following contact details:
Ordinary mail: CASIO Computer Co. Ltd.,
6-2, Hon-machi 1-chome, Shibuya-ku,
Tokyo 151-8543, Japan
Email address:
app1+casio-watches@casio.co.jp
You may contact our DPO by:
Ordinary mail: CASIO Computer Co. Ltd.,
Address: 6-2, Hon-machi 1-chome, Shibuya-ku,
Tokyo 151-8543, Japan
Attention: Data Protection Officer
Email address:
dataprotection@casio.co.jp
2. Categories of Personal Data
When you use the App, we collect any information about you including Personal Data automatically transmitted from the App to our servers, specifically:
(i)
CASIO ID Data
:
This App requires you to register with and sign up for CASIO ID before you can use this App. You provide us with information including your name, email address registered with your CASIO ID (hereinafter jointly "CASIO ID Data"). The data is required to log in to the App with your CASIO ID, and is the only information that is transmitted to the App from your CASIO ID registration data.
(ii)
Profile Data
:
We collect and use your profile data registered by yourself with the App, including your birth date, height, weight, gender and any other profile data (hereinafter jointly "Profile Data") when you choose to provide the data;
(iii)
Product Information
:
We collect and use PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network), serial number, model name, time zone, system and setting data of the watch or other product used in combination with the App ("
Product
").
(iv)
Uploaded Data
:
We collect to images, pictures, videos, texts and any other information that you uploaded, posted, transmitted or otherwise made available on the App (hereinafter jointly "Uploaded Data"), if you provide so on the App.
(v)
Device Data
;
When you access or use our App, we collect and use your system or setting data (consent about privacy, push notification and access Device’s media storage) and other device information of your mobile device in which the App is installed (together with Product, collectively, "
Devices
") including device identifier, model name, OS version and the setting data of the Devices, and date and time of usage and access to the App, and other user usage data in the App (hereinafter jointly "Device Data").
(vi)
Location Data
:
We collect and access GPS and GNSS location data, Wi-Fi status information, such as information about Wi-Fi access points and base points near the Devices location, recorded by the Devices (hereinafter jointly "Location Data"), if you grant us access to your location. You can always remove our access using your Product or your Device settings. The data collected depending on the model of Devices you use. We also identify your location by using a variety of technologies, including GPS, GNSS the Wi-Fi points you are accessing the App through and mobile/cell tower triangulation.
(vii)
Activity Data
:
We collect and use the data, recorded in the App and Devices [*1], to estimate your health status like your heart rate, numbers or steps you take, VO2max, sleep stages, location data, date and time of activity, and other data recorded by sensors on your Product that can be used to make inferences about or detect the health status of an individual (including numerical data calculated from measurement of your activity data, hereinafter jointly "Activity Data"). The data collected varies depending on which Product you use. When your Product syncs with our App, data recorded on your Product is transferred from your Product to our servers.
(viii)
Form Data
:
We collect any other information relating to any individuals which you have provided us in any forms you may have submitted to us, or via other forms of interaction with you (hereinafter jointly "Form Data").
[*1] Depending on the model of Devices, certain activity data cannot be functionally recorded by the App and Devices. For example, if your Product does not have a heart rate sensor, your heart rate, VO2max, step count and/or sleep stage are not measured and recorded by the Devices and therefore is not collected and processed by us unless manually entered into the App by yourself.
3. Health and other Special Categories of Personal Data
To the extent that information we collect is health data or another special category of Personal Data subject to the applicable data privacy laws, we ask for your explicit consent to process the data. We obtain this consent separately when you take actions leading to our obtaining the data, for example, when you pair your Product to the App, grant us access to your exercise or activity data from the Third-party App. You can use your access settings and tools to withdraw your consent at any time, including by stopping use of a feature, removing our access to the Third-party App, unpairing your Products, or deleting your data or your CASIO ID.
4. Purpose of usage
We use your Personal Data for the following purposes ("
Purposes
");
(1)
Performance purposes
, i.e.:
to operate the App by providing you with the respective functionalities of the App; and
to make sure you are eligible and able to use the App in order to authenticate you when you use the App with your CASIO ID.
<Categories of Personal Data> CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Uploaded Data, Device Data, Product Information, Location Data, Activity Data and Form Data .
(2)
Quality Purposes
, i.e.:
to monitor, and maintain the performance of the App and Product in order to review and improve our product and services, including the App and Product;
to conduct user analyses for statistical, marketing, or other purposes for us to develop, review and improve the quality of and to promote sales of our products and services (including the App and Product);
<Categories of Personal Data> CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Uploaded Data, Device, Product Information, Location Data, Activity Data and Form Data.
(3)
Contact Purpose
, i.e.:
to get in contact with you concerning your queries, or for any security and fraud prevention purposes;
<Categories of Personal Data> CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Uploaded Data, Device Data, Product Information, Activity Data (excluding heartrate, step count, VO2max and any other data that can estimate your health status) and Form Data.
(4)
Marketing Purpose
, i.e.:
with your permission, as permitted by applicable law, to send you information materials (by email or via push notifications) by us and/or CASIO group entities about our and/or our CASIO group entities’ products, services (including our and/or CASIO group entities’ products and services which you have not yet used) as well as events and benefits (including special events, promotions and campaigns held by us or CASIO group entities) which might be of interest to you; and
to operate our User Data Platform (defined in paragraph 11 below) where your Personal Data is recorded combining with a CASIO ID in order to efficiently conduct the above mentioned marketing purposes and to improve your satisfaction with this App, our and/or CASIO group entities’ products and services. You can unsubscribe from these at any time in your device settings or in-app settings.
<Categories of Personal Data> CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Uploaded Data, Device Data, Product Information, Location Data and Activity Data (excluding heartrate, step count, VO2max and any other data that can estimate your health status).
If you - as the holder of parental responsibility - have agreed on behalf of your minor child, information of your child will not be processed for Marketing Purposes.
(5)
Profiling Purpose
, i.e.:
to provide you customized marketing, so that the products and services can be tailored to meet your needs and the recommendations and offers displayed via the App and other online activities can be customized accordingly by analysing the usage of the App and Devices; and
to conduct profiling your behavior with our User Data Platform in order to efficiently conduct the above mentioned marketing purposes and to improve your satisfaction with this App, our products and services. You can unsubscribe from these at any time in your device settings or in-app settings.
<Categories of Personal Data> CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Device Data, Uploaded Data, Product Information, Location Data, Activity Data (excluding heartrate, step count and any other data that can estimate your health status) and Form Data.
If you - as the holder of parental responsibility - have agreed on behalf of your minor child, information of your child will not be processed for Profiling Purposes.
We may share aggregated usage information with third parties for statistical and analytical purpose to develop, review and improve the products and services related to the App, provided such information cannot be used to identify specific individual.
5. Legal basis
We will process your Personal Data based on the explicit consent given by you. Alternatively, we will use your Personal Data for the purpose of rendering the requested contractual service and the performance of the contract as set forth in (1) to (3) of paragraph 4, acting on the basis of any other legal grounds, such as to comply with a legal obligation or a court order, or legitimate interest as set forth in (4) and (5) of paragraph 4, when permitted by applicable laws.
The withdrawal or revocation of your consent shall not affect the lawfulness of processing performed based on the explicit consent given by you, before your withdrawal. Upon withdrawal, your Personal Data could still be processed if there is a legal basis related to complying with a contractual obligation.
6. Management of Personal Data
We have taken steps to protect your Personal Data in an appropriate manner, including to protect personally identifiable information included in your Personal Data.
We have appropriate legal, organizational and technical security measures in place to prevent your Personal Data from being accidentally lost, used or accessed in an unauthorized way, improperly altered or disclosed. We also limit access to your Personal Data to employees, agents, contractors and other third parties who have a business need to know. They will only process your Personal Data on our instructions, and they are subject to a duty of confidentiality.
We have put in place procedures to deal with any suspect Personal Data breach and will notify you and any applicable regulator of a breach where we are legally required to do so.
We also establish the necessary rules to protect Personal Data, conducting trainings to our employees and taking other appropriate organizational, physical and technical security measures. If you would like to know more about the security measures implemented to protect your Personal Data, you can contact us and/or our DPO at the Contact Information described in paragraph 1.
We collect, use and disclose (including cross-border transfer) your Personal Data to the extent permitted or required under applicable laws. In addition to this Privacy Notice, we follow our “Privacy Policy”, which you will find at "
https://world.casio.com/privacy
".
7. Storage location
Your Personal Data is transmitted to and stored in a server operated by our service providers, which server may be located outside of your country. For more details, please see below.
