8. Disclosing Personal Data to third parties
Your Personal Data may be disclosed to CASIO group entities, service providers and subcontractors as necessary to accomplish the Purposes.
Additionally, we may disclose your Personal Data to any judicial or governmental authorities, courts, external advisors, and similar third parties, if so required by them, in accordance with any applicable laws, rules or regulations.
9. Cross-border transfers
Your Personal Data may be transferred to, and stored by, a third party outside the country where you live, or which you were in when you used this App. Such countries include the countries in which our affiliates, subsidiaries, service providers and subcontractors above are located.
10. Connection with third party’s apps
The App has a feature to connect the App with certain apps provided by a third party ("
Third Party Apps
") by linking your user account of the Third Party Apps in order to automatically send your Personal Data in whole or in part to such Third Party Apps. Such feature is enabled by setting your user account of the Third Party Apps on the App following the App’s guidance. In no event your Personal Data will be sent to any Third Party Apps without your permission and your setting to do so.
Your Personal Data sent to the Third Party Apps by such feature will be processed by a provider of such Third Party Apps pursuant to applicable terms of use, privacy policy and other terms and conditions set forth by such provider. (In such case, this Privacy Notice will not apply to you.)
Within this app, the above settings can be used to link to Google Fit, and apply the customer data collected within Google Fit within the various functions of this app. In such instances, Casio will use the customer data collected by Google Fit within this app in accordance with the “
Google Fit Developer and User Data Policy
” established by Google, including the section pertaining to “
Limited Uses of User Data
”. The data derived from Google Fit and its uses within this app are as defined below.
Data used within this app: step count, calories consumed, heart rate, distance traveled, movement speed
Uses of this data within this app: This data will be used for body weight, step count, and distance displays, as well as to calculate other activity values based on this data.
User data collected within this app can also be linked to various functions within Google Fit. In such instances, personal information will be handled within Google Fit in accordance with Google’s
privacy policy
.
11. Analytics
Adobe Analytics
We use Adobe Analytics ("
Adobe Analytics
"), an analytics service provided by Adobe Systems Software Ireland Limited, located in Ireland ("
Adobe
") for conducting user analyses. Adobe Analytics uses cookies, which are text files placed on your mobile device or other hardware device, or certain unique identifiers for your device to help us analyze how users use the App.
The privacy policy of Adobe for Adobe Analytics is as follows:
Official website of Adobe Analytics
Privacy Policy of Adobe Analytics
User Data Platform
The data collected when you use the App, i.e., CASIO ID Data, Profile Data, Uploaded Data and Activity Data (excluding heartrate, step count, VO2max and any other data that can estimate your health status) stated paragraph 2 in this Privacy Notice, are measured by Adobe Analytics, provided by Adobe and transferred to a user data platform, provided by Treasure Data Japan, Inc., located in Japan ("
User Data Platform
"). The data collected in the server of Adobe Analytics will be automatically transferred to the User Data Platform once a day. Then, the data will be replicated in the User Data Platform and the data unnecessary for Marketing purpose and Profiling Purpose will be deleted or redacted. The data originally transferred to the User Data Platform will be retained without any change (i.e., not redacted or deleted). In the User Data Platform, the Profile Data, Uploaded Data and Activity Data (excluding heartrate, step count, VO2max and any other data that can estimate your health status) in anonymized form are checked against data connected with CASIO ID which are already recorded on the database.
If a device identifier connected to the device data matches that of the data connected with the CASIO ID, the Uploaded Data will be recorded against each concerned user's CASIO ID. CASIO group entities may access the User Data Platform to use the data recorded with each user's CASIO ID to the extent necessary for marketing activities and analysis in the market countries of such CASIO group entities.
You can unsubscribe from these at any time in your device settings or in-app settings.
12. Opt-out / Refusal
Generally, the processing of your Personal Data is voluntary. However, if you do not provide your Personal Data, your user experience of the App may be different or the use may be impossible.
By selecting the appropriate setting on the App, you may refuse or opt-out of the processing of your Personal Data.
While you may disable the usage of analytics tools through your device settings, we currently does not respond to a "Do Not Track" signal in the HTTP header from the App due to the lack of industry standard on how to interpret that signal.
13. Retention period
Your Personal Data will be retained only for as long as necessary for accomplishment of the Purposes, or as allowed by law. However, we need to keep your Personal Data to comply with legal or regulatory obligations to which Casio are subject. Further, if a judicial action is initiated, your
Personal Data
may be stored until the end of such action, including any potential periods for appeal, and will then be deleted or archived as permitted by applicable law.
We will cease to retain and will delete and remove your Personal Data from our systems and records and/or take steps to properly anonymize it so that you can no longer be identified from it, once the Purpose of processing is fulfilled, or after we confirm your request for erasure, or after operation of the corresponding product or service ends.
14. Your rights
You have a number of legal rights in relation to your Personal Data. These rights may vary depending on where you are located and which data protection laws will apply to the relationship between you and us, but would typically include;
(i) the right to obtain information regarding the processing of your Personal Data and to access to your Personal Data;
(ii) the right to request that we rectify and/or update your Personal Data if it is inaccurate or incomplete;
(iii) the right to request that we erase your Personal Data;
(iv) the right to request that we restrict our processing of your Personal Data;
(v) the right to object to us about our processing of your Personal Data;
(vi) the right to receive a copy of any of your Personal Data where this is technically feasible;
(vii) the right to withdraw your consent to our processing of your Personal Data; and
(viii) the right to transmit your Personal Data received from us to another entity without hindrance from us.
You can exercise your rights by contacting us via post at CASIO Computer Co. Ltd., 6-2, Hon-machi 1-chome, Shibuya-ku, Tokyo 151-8543, Japan or at the following email address:
app1+casio-watches@casio.co.jp
, or through the information about us described in paragraph 1. You can also lodge a complaint with the data protection regulator if you think that any of your rights have been infringed by us.
15. Children’s Privacy
If you have not yet reached the age of legal majority but are at least 16 years of age or as defined by applicable laws and legal requirements ("Under Age"), certain parts of this Privacy Notice also apply to the parent, legal guardian of a child or the holder of parental responsibility over you ("Parent"). However, if you are between 13 and this age threshold to give a lawful consent, we will request your Parent consent to using this App. If you are below the age of 13, we do not offer the services regarding this App to you. If we learn we have mistakenly or unintentionally collected or received Personal Data from a child without appropriate consent, we will delete it.
If you are Under Age, certain legal restrictions may apply and we may need the authorization of your Parent in order to process your Personal Data with regard to provision of the App. Therefore, we collect the Personal Data with regard to your Parent.
16. Changes to this Privacy Notice
We reserve the right to make any changes to this Privacy Notice. You will be notified adequately of any such changes. Such changes are effective immediately unless a different effective date is stated, however, if specifically required to do so by applicable laws, we will seek your prior consent before adopting such changes in respect of your Personal Data.
ADDITIONAL NOTICE FOR CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS
Last Updated: March 8, 2023
California’s consumer privacy laws, California’s "Shine the Light" law, and the California Online Privacy Protection Act provide consumers who are California residents with specific rights regarding their personal data. If you are a California resident, this Additional Notice for California Residents ("Additional Notice") describes your rights and explains how to exercise those rights and applies to California residents.
This Additional Notice forms part of the Privacy Notice for CASIO WATCHES last updated as of March 8, 2023 ("Privacy Notice") and prevails over any conflicting provisions in the Privacy Notice as they may apply to California residents.
1. Information we collect
Paragraph 2 of the Privacy Notice lists the categories of Personal Data we may collect from California residents. You are entitled to know whether we have collected and shared certain categories of information for a business purpose. In the 12 months preceding the last updated date of the Privacy Notice, we have collected or received the following categories of Personal Data about you:
(A)
Identifiers
[*2]
:
name and email address registered with CASIO ID, device identifier of your Device;
(B)
Personal information categories listed in the California Customer Records statute
(Cal Civ Code § 1798.80(e))[*3], name registered with CASIO ID;
(C)
Protected classification characteristics under California or federal law
[*4]
:
your date of birth, gender registered with CASIO ID;
(D)
Commercial Information
[*5] : Product Information (serial number, model name of the Product you have bought and registered with the App)
(E)
Biometric information
[*6] : your activity, sleep or health data, including step count, heart rate, VO2max data, sleep stage, active minutes;
(F)
Internet or other similar network activity
[*7] : the date and time of usage, activity and access to the App and other user activity data in the App and Devices;
(G)
Geolocation data
[*8] : your location data, including GPS, GNSS location data, Wi-Fi status information recorded by the Device ;
(H)
Sensory Data
[*9] : your profile photo or other photos and videos;
(I)
Professional or employment-related information
[*10] : Not Applicable;
(J)
Non-public education information
(per the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (20 U.S.C. Section 1232g, 34 C.F.R. Part 99)) [*11] : Not Applicable; and
(K)
Inferences drawn from other personal information
[*12] : the number of calories you burned, distance you travelled, sleep insights, and personalized activity goals, profiling data reflecting your preferences, behavior, attitudes in connection with the App, our Products, services and advertisement.
[*2] A. Identifiers: i.e., a real name, alias, postal address, unique personal identifier, online identifier, Internet Protocol (IP) address, email address, account name, or other similar identifiers.
[*3] B. Personal information categories listed in the California Customer Records statute (Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.80(e)) : i.e.. a name, address, telephone number, education, or employment.
Some personal information included in this category may overlap with other categories.
[*4] C. Protected classification characteristics under California or federal law : i.e., age (e. g. 40 years or older), race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or creed, marital status, sex (including gender, gender identity, gender expression, pregnancy or childbirth and related medical conditions), veteran or military status.
[*5] D. Commercial information : i.e., Records of personal property, products or services purchased, obtained, or considered, or other purchasing or consuming histories or tendencies.
[*6] E. Biometric information : i.e., Genetic, physiological, behavioral, and biological characteristics, such as DNA sequences, fingerprints, facial geometry, voiceprints, iris or retina scans, and sleep, health or exercise data
[*7]
F. Internet or other similar network activity: i.e.,
Browsing history, search history, information on a consumer’s interaction with a website, application, or advertisement
[*8]
G. Geolocation data
: i.e., Physical location or movements.
[*9] H.
Sensory data
: i.e., Audio, electronic, visual, thermal, olfactory, or similar information.
[*10] I. Professional or employment-related information: i.e., Current or past job history or performance evaluations.
[*12] J. Non-public education information (per the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (20 U.S.C. Section 1232g, 34 C.F.R. Part 99)) is i.e.: education records directly related to a student maintained by an educational institution or party acting on its behalf, such as grades, transcripts, class lists, student schedules, student identification codes, student financial information, or student disciplinary records.
[*13] K. Inferences drawn from other personal information: i.e., Profile reflecting a person’s preferences, characteristics, psychological trends, predispositions, behavior, attitudes, intelligence, abilities, and aptitudes.
2. How We Use Your Personal Data
Paragraph 4 of the Privacy Notice lists the business or commercial Purposes for which we may collect and process your Personal Data.
3. Personal Data We Share
We never sell your Personal Data. We share your Personal Data with certain third parties as described in the Privacy Notice. During the 12 months preceding the last updated date of the Privacy Notice, we disclosed the following categories of Personal Data within the scope of the Purposes described in paragraph 4 of the Privacy Notice:
Below we describe: (i) the categories of Personal Data that we may disclose for our operational business purposes; (ii) the service providers and CASIO group entity to whom we may disclose such Personal Data for our operational business purposes.
(1) (i) A. Identifiers, i.e.; name and email address registered with CASIO ID, device identifier of your Device; (ii) Service providers, namely Amazon Web Services Japan G.K., Adobe System Ireland Limited, Salesforce.com Co., Ltd. and Treasure Data Japan, Inc. and CASIO group entity in the United States, namely Casio America, Inc.
(2) Internet or other electronic network activity information
Example: Date/time of your access to the App
Service providers and CASIO group entity to whom your Personal Data may be disclosed:
Adobe Systems Ireland Limited, Treasure Data Japan, Inc., Salesforce.com Co., Ltd, and Casio America, Inc.
Third Parties to whom your Personal Data may be sold:
Advertising networks
We do not sell the Personal Data of California residents including the residents under 16 years of age, as the term “sell” is defined under California law. We share your Personal Data with certain third parties as described in this Privacy Notice.
California Residents’ Privacy Rights
Subject to certain exceptions, California residents have certain rights with respect to their personal information, including the right to:
Request access to copies of your personal information;
Request access to information about what categories of personal information we have collected from you, the categories of sources of such information, the business or commercial purposes for which we have collected or sold your personal information, the categories of third parties with whom we have shared your personal information, the categories of personal information that we have sold about you, and the categories of personal information that we have disclosed about you for a business purpose;
Request deletion of your personal information;
Request to opt out of the sale of your personal information; and
Not be discriminated against because you exercised any of your California privacy rights.
You can make requests as follows:
E-mail address:
app1+casio-watches@casio.co.jp
Toll-free telephone number: (800) 706-2534
To help protect your privacy and maintain security, we will take steps to verify your identity before granting you access to your Personal Data or complying with your deletion request.
Upon receiving an access or deletion request from you, we will first verify your identity by requiring you to submit your name and e-mail address, and by matching the information you provide with what we already have on file.
If you use an authorized agent to make an access or deletion request on your behalf, we may require the authorized agent to provide proof that you gave the agent signed permission to make the request. Also, we may require you to either (1) verify your own identity directly with us (as described above), or (2) directly confirm with us that you provided the authorized agent permission to submit the request.
Your App and Device settings also let you exercise your right to access your Personal Data and to understand how we collect, use and disclose it, and exercise your right to delete Personal Data.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Addendum or our privacy practices, please contact us at our office address or e-mail address described in Paragraph 1 of the Privacy Notice.
